						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up by the side of the railway line in the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1681, Pramādi, Śrāvaṇa, śu. 10, Friday, corresponding to 1759 A.D., August 3.</p>						

						<p>States that the boundaries of the village were marked and the <hi rend="italic">jayastaṁbha</hi> was set up by Raṅgarāju, son of Gārlapāṭi Guruvarāju.</p>						

						</summary>
